# Autopoet.Spine

  The app's supervision **spine** ŌĆö one `.work`-authored `Supervisor` that owns every
  stateful domain process (the log, history, auth, profile, the shadow learners, the
  desktop I/O engines, the discovery beacon, the desks). The `.ex` `Autopoet.Application`
  is now just the OTP bootstrap: it boots `Nexus.Config`, then starts `Nexus.Server`
  (which owns HTTP + compiles this very module at bringup), THIS spine, and the window.

  Split of concerns:
    * `Autopoet.Application` (.ex, the irreducible OTP `mod:` entry) ŌĆö boots the runtime
      boundaries: `Nexus.Server` (HTTP) + `Autopoet.Window` (the kill-switch) + one-shot
      world seeds.
    * `Autopoet.Spine` (this, .work) ŌĆö the app's own brain/domain processes, authored as
      a workbook so the same tree runs on the local desktop nexus AND the workbooks.sh
      cloud nexus (a redeploy recompiles it at bringup ŌĆö no scattered `.ex` to ship).

  Authored as a bare top-level `defmodule` code block (NOT wrapped in `server :spine`):
  the literate parser recognizes `defmodule X do` as a block opener and closes it at the
  unique column-0 `end`, so the module's body must (and does) stay indented. A `server`
  wrapper would nest a second column-0 `end` and break the block boundary. `compile_workbook`
  collects this `defmodule` and compiles it to its own canonical name, `Autopoet.Spine`.

  Boot ordering (why a `.work` module can supervise boot-critical processes):
  `Nexus.Server.start_link` runs `bringup` SYNCHRONOUSLY ŌĆö compiling every `.work` BEAM
  unit, this one included ŌĆö before it returns. `Autopoet.Application` orders `Nexus.Server`
  as its FIRST child, and pre-compiles the tier once at start so `Autopoet.Spine` is loaded
  before its child slot (an explicit map spec, `start:` mfa, no upfront `child_spec/1`) runs.

defmodule Autopoet.Spine do
  @moduledoc """
  The app's supervision spine: one `Supervisor` owning every stateful domain process.
  Started by `Autopoet.Application` AFTER `Nexus.Server` (which compiles this module at
  bringup). The cloud profile (`AUTOPOET_TARGET=cloud`) drops the desktop-only I/O
  engines (mic STT + realtime Voice) ŌĆö the same tree, minus the hardware lanes.
  """
  use Supervisor

  def start_link(opts) when is_map(opts) do
    Supervisor.start_link(__MODULE__, opts, name: __MODULE__)
  end

  @impl true
  def init(opts) do
    port = Map.fetch!(opts, :port)

    children =
      [
        Autopoet.Log,
        Autopoet.History,
        Autopoet.Auth,
        Autopoet.Profile
      ] ++
        desktop_io() ++
        [
          # Autopoet.Watchdog is now a `worker :watchdog` block (backend/watchdog.work) ŌĆö
          # the nexus Worker.Supervisor owns it, started at bringup, so it is NOT a spine
          # child anymore (P3).
          Autopoet.Requests,
          Autopoet.Capture,
          # Autopoet.Snapshot is now a `worker :snapshot` block (backend/snapshot.work) ŌĆö
          # the nexus Worker.Supervisor owns it (P3).
          Autopoet.Shadow.Hebb,
          Autopoet.Shadow.Surprise,
          Autopoet.Shadow.Outcomes,
          {Autopoet.Discovery, port}
        ] ++ [Autopoet.Desks] ++ desk()

    # max_restarts headroom: tests hard-kill the three shadow learners to force
    # cold/reboot paths ŌĆö three near-simultaneous restarts must not take down the tree.
    Supervisor.init(children, strategy: :one_for_one, max_restarts: 10)
  end

  @doc "Is this the cloud profile (a vendored Fly machine), not the desktop?"
  def cloud?, do: System.get_env("AUTOPOET_TARGET") == "cloud"

  # Desktop-only I/O children (mic STT + realtime Voice) ŌĆö dropped in the cloud.
  # Filtered to modules that actually exist so a mid-refactor tree (a renamed or
  # deleted I/O module) degrades to missing audio, never a boot crash.
  defp desktop_io do
    if cloud?() do
      []
    else
      # Qwen3-TTS is the product engine. Kokoro is booted ONLY when the dev toggle
      # asks for it (WB_VOICE=kokoro or data/voice-engine) ŌĆö a comparison lens, never
      # the default.
      base = [Autopoet.Stt, Autopoet.Voice, Autopoet.QwenTts, Autopoet.Affect]
      base = if Autopoet.VoiceEngine.kokoro?(), do: [Autopoet.Kokoro | base], else: base

      Enum.filter(base, fn mod ->
        Code.ensure_loaded?(mod) ||
          (IO.puts("autopoet: desktop I/O child #{inspect(mod)} missing ŌĆö skipped") && false)
      end)
    end
  end

  # The always-on trading desk (day/night market cycle) ŌĆö opt-in via AUTOPOET_DESK=1
  # (machine-identity enablement, like PORT/WB_DATA). Never on in tests by default.
  defp desk do
    if System.get_env("AUTOPOET_DESK") == "1", do: [Autopoet.Desk], else: []
  end
end
